[Area of a Trapezoid]
Equivalent to half of a trapezoid's height times the sum of its base lengths.
A = (1/2)(h)(b1 + b2).

––––––––––––-––––––––––––-––––––––––––-––––––––––––-––––––––––––-––––––––––––-–

Figure: http://i.imgur.com/pKbxMyk.png

The area of the figure abouve is 18 square feet.
How long is the other base?

b1.....................
A = (1/2)(h)(b1 + b2)
18 = (1/2)(6)(b1 + 2)
18 = 3(b1 + 2)
18 = 3(b1) + 6
12 = 3(b1)
4 = b1

