A trapezoid has an area of 1875 square inches. If the trapezoid has bases
measuring 100 inches and 50 inches, what is the height of the trapezoid?

A..........................
A = (1/2)(h)(b1 + b2)
1875 = (1/2)(h)(100 + 50)
1875 = 0.5(100 + 50)(h)
1875 = h(50 + 25)
1875 = 50h + 25h
1875 = 75h
25 = h

