A trapezoid has an area of 80 square centimeters. If the trapezoid has a base
measuring 8 centimeters and a height of 8 centimeters, what is the length of
the other base?

A = (1/2)(h)(b1 + b2)
80 = (1/2)(8)(8 + b2)
80 = (1/2)(8 * (8 + b2))
80 = (1/2)(64 + 8b2)
80 = 32 + 4b2
48 = 4b2
12 = b2
